**Title:** COM – LockPick Community – SAINTCON

**Description:** 
The LockPick Community promotes a security mindset through lockpicking activities at SAINTCON. Participants can progress from novice to adept while following the Lock Pickers United belt system.

**Key Points:**
- **Facilitators:** k33n and N8tonium
- **Purpose:** To foster critical thinking and skills in lockpicking.
- **Learning Structure:**
  - **Beginner to Expert:** Participants can start with no prior knowledge.
  - **Hands-On Classes:** Engaging sessions to learn the basics.
  - **Skill Advancement:** Structured belt system for progression.
  
**Tools:**
- **Provided:** Essential tools and locks are available.
- **Recommended for Advanced:** Personal lockpicking sets for more complex locks.

**FAQs:**
- **Belt System:** Follows the Lock Pickers United system from white to black belt, with achievements recognized by micro-badges.

**Participation:** Welcomes beginners and experienced pickers, emphasizing a mindset to learn.

**Hours of Operation:**
- **Monday:** Expo Closed
- **Tuesday:** 10:30 AM – 5:00 PM
- **Wednesday:** 10:30 AM – 5:00 PM
- **Thursday:** 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM
- **Friday:** 9:00 AM – 11:00 AM

**What You Will Learn:**
- Lock systems and vulnerabilities.
- Techniques for picking basic and advanced locks.

**Additional Offerings:**
- MiniBadge available at the community booth.
- Desktop wallpaper for download.

**Links:**
- **Community Information:** [Visit LockPick Community](https://saintcon.org/com-lockpick-community/)
- **Belt System Info:** [Join the Community](http://lpubelts.com)

**Background Image:** Lockpick-themed desktop wallpaper available for download. 

**Overall Vision:** Unlock both locks and personal potential in the realm of physical security at SAINTCON.